cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.LO. 

The paper combines deep learning, probability theory, and fuzzy modeling to develop a data-driven approach for modeling nonlinear systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is focused on developing and applying machine learning algorithms. The paper also uses optimization methods, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well. The use of extreme learning machines and fuzzy modeling indicates that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control), respectively. Finally, the paper proposes a new method for clustering hidden features, which could also place it in the cs.LO (Optimization and Control) sub-category.
